# MITRE ATT&CK Mapping

This directory documents how the simulated attacks performed in the Enterprise SOC Lab map to the MITRE ATT&CK framework.

## Objectives

- Map observed attacker behavior to MITRE ATT&CK.
- Demonstrate understanding of adversary tactics and techniques.
- Show how Elastic Security detections align with real-world attack stages.

## Covered Tactics

- Reconnaissance
- Discovery
- Credential Access
- Initial Access
- Lateral Movement

## Covered Techniques

| Technique | ID |
|-----------|----|
| Active Scanning | T1595.001 |
| Network Service Discovery | T1046 |
| Password Spraying | T1110.003 |
| Valid Accounts | T1078 |
| Network Share Discovery | T1135 |

For detailed mappings, see the files in this folder.
